# mavlink_generator — core rules

Rust MAVLink code generator with CLI (`src/`) and Tauri desktop UI (`ui/`). Shared logic lives in `src/driver.rs`.

## Validate changes

```bash
# Rust core (repo root)
cargo fmt && cargo check && cargo test

# UI (when touching ui/)
cd ui && pnpm build
```

## Do not edit

- `generated/` — regenerate via `cargo run`
- `mavlink/` — upstream submodule
- `private/` — gitignored personal notes

## Minimize scope

- One concern per change; match existing patterns in the touched module
- Adding a language requires changes in `src/generate/mod.rs`, `runtime.rs`, `examples.rs`, `templates/`, and `tests/generator.rs`
- Version bumps: sync `Cargo.toml`, `ui/package.json`, `ui/src-tauri/tauri.conf.json`

## Key entry points

- CLI: `src/main.rs` → `driver::run_generate`
- Library API: `src/lib.rs`
- UI backend: `ui/src-tauri/src/lib.rs` (invokes `mavlink_generator::driver`)
- UI frontend: `ui/src/api/commands.ts`
